The only issue I had was how they handled the return of Palpatine. His return/reveal should have been more dramatic. But for some reason itâ€™s included in the opening crawl. Other than that, TROS was easily the best of new trilogy, and even better than Dom of the prequels. Thank you JJ! You brought Star Wars Back!

I love it.  I think JJ did a great job wrapping things up.  Chewy finally getting his medal was precious.

I dont agree with the critics on this. I love this movie. I loved force awakens and last jedi as well but this movie is messy and emotional and action packed and epic, and everything i wanted in the skywalker saga finale. Forget criticism and just be ready for a fun ride

It was a good Star Wars movie. Wrapped things up and I cared what happened. I know critics want the movie to be like Last Jedi, but Star Wars did not become a beloved franchise because it was dark and joyless like Last Jedi.

I've read all the criticisms of this film and honestly don't see how they apply. It's about redemption, family, abandonment, knowledge from elders getting passed down, friendship, and unity against tyranny. All things we need to hear right now. As a fan of Star Wars and one who grew up during the time of the prequel trilogy, me and my family and friends loved it.

Very convoluted. Lots of exposition. Some great twists but they didn't feel earned to me, in part because we didn't have a lot of down time to remember the bonds between the characters and to establish an emotional connection to the new ones. Some good gags and some fun moments in the mix, but not a strong movie overall.

Given the divisiveness of The Last Jedi, J.J. Abrams had a huge mountain to overcome in The Rise Of Skywalker, but he absolutely did so with dignity & style.  While there are certainly a few rushed bits in the first act (hell, he had to cram an entire movie's worth of character development into a couple scenes since the main trio had never fully interacted before), the end result is a film that is a visual spectacle with a great story the fans deserved.  Would it have been great if many of these seeds were planted during the boring space-chase of TLJ?  Oh hell yeah, but nevertheless I'm ecstatic that we got here in the end!  Definitely go see this film!
great job JJ. Parts were a little cliche, but there was a lot to wrap up so I'm not mad at it. good job sprinkling in appropriate levels of humor throughout the movie.
Full of action, a little too full. Almost no time to let big moments resonate. Does a good job as the end of this trilogy, but in no way feels like an end to the Skywalker saga
